          "answer": "Copenhagen is one of Europe's most expensive capitals. Minimum budget (hostel, eating at markets and supermarkets, public transport): €80-100/day. Mid-range budget (simple hotel, mix of restaurants and markets): €150-200/day. Comfortable budget (good hotel, restaurants, activities, museums): €250+/day. The key to saving: eat at Torvehallerne and markets, and use a bicycle instead of the metro when the weather allows."
